# Security

- **Phase gate**: complete [docs/security/phase-gate-checklist.md](../../docs/security/phase-gate-checklist.md) before each feature phase — see [19-security-phase-gate](19-security-phase-gate.mdc)
- **RBAC** (minimum) / **ABAC** (when needed); **Least Privilege** always
- Passwords: strong hashing (Argon2/bcrypt)
- **JWT** short-lived + rotation; **refresh tokens** separate and revocable
- **MFA** on sensitive accounts
- **Rate limiting** on public endpoints and authentication
- Mandatory protections: **CSRF**, **XSS**, **SQL Injection** (parameterized queries/ORM) — [docs/security/](../../docs/security/README.md)
- **IDOR**: object-level authorization on every ID-based route
- **CORS**: explicit allowlist in production — not a substitute for authz
- **Media uploads**: max **10 MB**/image; server-side EXIF strip — [media-uploads.md](../../docs/security/media-uploads.md)
- **Defense in depth**: no single-layer security — [security-chain-failures.md](../../docs/security/security-chain-failures.md)
- Cover **OWASP Top 10** in sensitive reviews
- **Never** log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, PII)
